ControlPropertyState.AutoRuleBindingString: If(Self.Layout = Layout.Horizontal, Min(320, Self.Width - 60), Min(320, Self.Height - 60))

Rules.InvariantScript:
If(
    Text(
        DateAdd(
            gblFirstDayInView,
            ThisItem.Value,
            Days
        ),
        "mmmm"
    ) <> Text(
        gblFirstDayOfMonth,
        "mmmm"
    ),
    Transparent,
    DateAdd(
        gblFirstDayInView,
        ThisItem.Value
    ) = gblStartDate || DateAdd(
        gblFirstDayInView,
        ThisItem.Value
    ) = gblEndDate,
    DateRangeComponent.StylingProperty.DatePicker.DaysLabel.SelectedFill,
    DateAdd(
        gblFirstDayInView,
        ThisItem.Value
    ) in DateRangeComponent.SelectedDates.DateValue,
   DateRangeComponent.StylingProperty.DatePicker.DaysLabel.RangesFill,
    DateRangeComponent.StylingProperty.DatePicker.DaysLabel.Fill
)

If(
    DateAdd(
        gblFirstDayInView,
        ThisItem.Value
    ) = gblStartDate || DateAdd(
        gblFirstDayInView,
        ThisItem.Value
    ) = gblEndDate,
    DateRangeComponent.StylingProperty.DatePicker.DaysLabel.SelectedColor,
    Text(
        DateAdd(
            gblFirstDayInView,
            ThisItem.Value
        ),
        "dddd"
    ) = "Sunday",
    DateRangeComponent.StylingProperty.DatePicker.DaysLabel.SundayColor,
    DateRangeComponent.StylingProperty.DatePicker.DaysLabel.OtherDaysColor
)

{

    HeadingLabel: gblControlStyles.ControlLabel,
    DatePicker: gblControlStyles.DateRange,
    CloseIcon: gblControlStyles.CloseIcon,
    ErrorIcon: gblControlStyles.ErrorIcon,
    ErrorMessagePopup: gblControlStyles.ErrorMessagePopup
}
